# Vite "seed" mode env file, loaded by `vite --mode seed` (the `dev:seed` /
# `build:seed` / `preview:seed` npm scripts). Setting VITE_SEED makes the app
# populate localStorage with a realistic fake dataset at startup — several
# namespaces, each with notes of varying length and shape — so the UI can be
# exercised against lifelike content while debugging. See `src/dev/seed.ts`.
#
# This file is committed on purpose: it carries no secrets, only the dev flag,
# and never loads under a plain `make dev` / production build.
VITE_SEED=true
